The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Corporate Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Corporate Briefs
                              
	 Tata Power has reported a net profit after tax of Rs 869.90 crore for the year ended March 31, 2008, an increase of 24.8 per cent from Rs 696.80 crore in the year-ago period, it said in a filing to the Bombay Stock Exchange. Its total income for fiscal 2007-08 stood at Rs 6,381.75 crore against Rs 5,059.31 crore in 2006-07. The companys board of directors has recommended a dividend of Rs 10.50 per share to the shareholders for the year ended March 31, 2008.                            
	 IFGL Refractories Ltd has paid Rs 1.50 crore as the first instalment of advance income tax for the current fiscal. The amount paid is about 11 per cent higher than what was paid for the corresponding instalment in 2007-2008.                            
	 The management board of Public Relations Organisation International (PROI) has selected three new partner agencies  Perception Management International Sdn Bhd, ZEGO Communication Strategies Ltd and Active Public Relations amp; Marketing Communications Consultancy  based in Malaysia, Turkey and Dubai, respectively.                            
	 Subhash Projects and Marketing Ltd (SPML) has forayed into road construction projects on built-own-operate basis with the four-laning of the Jaora Nayagaon state highway by Madhya Pradesh Road Development Corporation.                             
	 SatNav Technologies aims to bring to the mass market a variety of navigation solutions that will cater to consumers who can access SatNav products in their mobiles, cars and computers.                             
	 Aksh Optifibre , in association with MTNL, has launched icontrol in Delhi and Mumbai, which enables consumers to control the television and request for programmes of their choice.                             
	 Genesis Colors has offered minority stake in the company to Sequoia Capital Fund, Mayfield Fund and Silicon Valley Bank for Rs 110 crore.                             
	 Jet Airways has started daily services from Mumbai to San Francisco via Shanghai, becoming the first Indian carrier to operate daily non-stop flights to Shanghai from Mumbai and onward to San Francisco.                             
	 CavinKare has launched Indica Singles herbal hair colour available in single sachet packs priced at Rs 6.                            
	 Godrej has launched tamper-proof video door phones in Calcutta that enables one to identify the person waiting at the door before opening it. The product is priced at Rs 8,000 upwards.                                                                                                                  ADVERTISEMENT                   
